Mission for Essential Drugs and Supplies, a leading regional medicines and medical equipment supplier, will get an enhanced quality certification after undergoing a successful inspection by the Kenya Bureau of Standards.The firm is transitioning to the new ISO 9001:2015 from its present ISO 9001:2008, which will give a stronger vote of confidence in its quality management. Meds managing director Paschal Manyuru says after the inspection last year, Kebs recertified the organisation for another two years.&ldquo;The achievement goes a long way to confirm that our products and services are safe, reliable and of good quality,&rdquo; he said.